This paper discusses the adoption of information system security innovations in organizations, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also incorporates theoretical models related to technology acceptance, planned behavior, and organizational environment, which suggests that it may also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE), cyber security (cs.CY), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and information retrieval (cs.IR). However, since the focus is primarily on security adoption, cs.CR is the most likely category.
